WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.859
This morning, the book of 2 Timothy,

00:00:02.859 --> 00:00:05.199
the book of 2 Timothy, it'll be a theme verse

00:00:05.199 --> 00:00:07.800
or a theme really message this morning,

00:00:07.800 --> 00:00:11.640
kind of overviewing the entire thought for the new year.

00:00:11.640 --> 00:00:13.319
And I'm thankful for the opportunity

00:00:13.319 --> 00:00:17.920
to be looking forward to what God has in store for us.

00:00:17.920 --> 00:00:20.280
In many ways, I believe that you would probably

00:00:20.280 --> 00:00:22.440
echo the statement, it's hard to believe

00:00:22.440 --> 00:00:25.979
that today is the last day of 2023.

00:00:25.979 --> 00:00:30.459
And for many of us, as we flip the calendar tomorrow, 2024,

00:00:30.459 --> 00:00:32.419
we think about just our lives

00:00:32.419 --> 00:00:34.419
and we think about all that has happened

00:00:34.419 --> 00:00:36.299
and see where we are.

00:00:36.299 --> 00:00:39.159
And we certainly rejoice in the goodness of God,

00:00:39.159 --> 00:00:41.740
the opportunity and privilege that he has given us

00:00:41.740 --> 00:00:44.459
to serve him yet for another day.

00:00:44.459 --> 00:00:46.939
And we look forward to what God will do.

00:00:46.939 --> 00:00:49.860
Of course, we expect that God will continue

00:00:49.860 --> 00:00:50.700
to do great things.

00:00:50.700 --> 00:00:52.500
We look forward to a soon return,

00:00:52.500 --> 00:00:54.340
and it could be that we never even flip

00:00:54.340 --> 00:00:55.560
the calendar to tomorrow.

00:00:56.159 --> 00:00:57.560
It could be that the Lord returns still today

00:00:57.560 --> 00:00:59.439
and that'd be okay with me, amen.

00:00:59.439 --> 00:01:01.599
And we certainly look forward to the imminent,

00:01:01.599 --> 00:01:03.840
the soon return of the Lord Jesus Christ.

00:01:03.840 --> 00:01:06.980
But each year, somewhere around September, October,

00:01:06.980 --> 00:01:09.400
I begin to fervently seek the Lord

00:01:09.400 --> 00:01:12.379
with regard to a theme for the next year.

00:01:12.379 --> 00:01:13.839
And I've done that every year

00:01:13.839 --> 00:01:15.360
that God's given me the opportunity

00:01:15.360 --> 00:01:17.720
to pastor here at Fellowship Baptist Church.

00:01:17.720 --> 00:01:21.220
And I have thanked the Lord for his guidance

00:01:21.220 --> 00:01:22.680
and for his direction.

00:01:22.680 --> 00:01:25.519
And I desire that God will provide us

00:01:25.519 --> 00:01:28.120
with an annual church theme that will help us

00:01:28.120 --> 00:01:32.360
to be encouraged and challenged throughout the entire year.

00:01:32.360 --> 00:01:34.959
And very quickly, if you think back,

00:01:34.959 --> 00:01:36.139
those some of you have been here

00:01:36.139 --> 00:01:38.040
since the beginning of me being here.

00:01:38.040 --> 00:01:40.500
And in 2012, I got here in August of 2011.

00:01:40.500 --> 00:01:43.480
So the first full calendar year was 2012.

00:01:43.480 --> 00:01:46.959
And our theme that year was Standing on His Promises.

00:01:46.959 --> 00:01:49.319
And I'm so thankful for the promises of God.

00:01:49.319 --> 00:01:52.400
And we were reminded each week of various promises

00:01:53.080 --> 00:01:54.199
that God has given to us.

00:01:54.199 --> 00:01:56.800
And we find that Peter said they're exceeding great

00:01:56.800 --> 00:01:58.879
and precious promises.

00:01:58.879 --> 00:02:01.279
And we can thank God for the promises

00:02:01.279 --> 00:02:02.199
that he's given us.

00:02:02.199 --> 00:02:05.599
In 2013, we turned to the book of Esther

00:02:05.599 --> 00:02:07.959
and throughout the year preached from the book of Esther

00:02:07.959 --> 00:02:11.619
dealing with the theme of for such a time as this.

00:02:11.619 --> 00:02:15.080
And God no doubt has put us here for such a time

00:02:15.080 --> 00:02:16.520
even as he did Esther.

00:02:16.520 --> 00:02:18.759
And what an opportunity that God has given us

00:02:18.759 --> 00:02:21.759
to serve him even as he did Esther.

00:02:21.759 --> 00:02:24.600
In 2014, the book of John, he must increase.

00:02:24.600 --> 00:02:26.440
What a great challenging statement

00:02:26.440 --> 00:02:29.399
as John the Baptist is standing there in John three

00:02:29.399 --> 00:02:31.160
and the discussion that takes place.

00:02:31.160 --> 00:02:33.320
And he looks to Jesus and he says of Jesus,

00:02:33.320 --> 00:02:36.679
he must increase, but I must decrease.

00:02:36.679 --> 00:02:39.119
And really it's all about the Lord Jesus Christ.

00:02:39.119 --> 00:02:41.639
And we studied through the book of John in 2014.

00:02:41.639 --> 00:02:44.440
In 2015 and 2016, we looked at the book of Acts.

00:02:44.440 --> 00:02:48.639
In the first part of the series in 2015,

00:02:48.639 --> 00:02:50.600
we dealt with Acts one through 12.

00:02:50.679 --> 00:02:53.160
And we dealt with the thought of boldness

00:02:53.160 --> 00:02:57.039
to speak thy word and oh, how we need that boldness.

00:02:57.039 --> 00:02:59.919
God's promised to be with us.

00:02:59.919 --> 00:03:02.880
And we find that throughout the scriptures

00:03:02.880 --> 00:03:06.759
that the disciples and Paul himself prayed for boldness

00:03:06.759 --> 00:03:09.339
and how we ought to pray for boldness.

00:03:09.339 --> 00:03:12.399
The latter part of the book of Acts in 2016,

00:03:12.399 --> 00:03:14.080
we looked at Acts 13 through 28.

00:03:14.080 --> 00:03:17.320
We dealt with the subject of I believe God.

00:03:17.320 --> 00:03:20.039
I hope that you still believe God, amen.

00:03:20.039 --> 00:03:21.679
God is trustworthy.

00:03:21.679 --> 00:03:24.080
He's always done what he said he would do.

00:03:24.080 --> 00:03:27.360
He's always going to do what he said he will do.

00:03:27.360 --> 00:03:29.000
And he is a trustworthy God.

00:03:29.000 --> 00:03:31.279
And Paul stands up at the end of the book of Acts

00:03:31.279 --> 00:03:36.039
in the 27th chapter and he says, I believe God.

00:03:36.039 --> 00:03:38.559
And oh, how we need some of God's people today

00:03:38.559 --> 00:03:41.520
to have that same level of faith and confidence

00:03:41.520 --> 00:03:42.880
in what God has said.

00:03:42.880 --> 00:03:45.000
In 2017, increase our faith.

00:03:45.000 --> 00:03:46.199
And we dealt with a number of things

00:03:46.199 --> 00:03:48.199
throughout the calendar year that God would use

00:03:48.199 --> 00:03:50.080
in our lives to increase our faith.

00:03:50.080 --> 00:03:52.360
The Bible says, so then faith cometh by hearing

00:03:52.360 --> 00:03:54.440
and hearing by the word of God.

00:03:54.440 --> 00:03:57.880
And God will use his word to increase our faith.

00:03:57.880 --> 00:04:00.559
And we desire, even as the disciples said,

00:04:00.559 --> 00:04:02.880
Lord, teach us to pray, but then they said,

00:04:02.880 --> 00:04:05.800
Lord, increase our faith.

00:04:05.800 --> 00:04:08.240
And oh, that God would help us to believe him

00:04:08.240 --> 00:04:09.080
and to trust him.

00:04:09.080 --> 00:04:11.339
In 2018, count your blessings.

00:04:11.339 --> 00:04:14.199
And in that particular calendar year,

00:04:14.199 --> 00:04:19.200
we said that we desired to have a number of reasons

00:04:19.359 --> 00:04:24.059
every week of the year, a new reason that we can rejoice.

00:04:24.059 --> 00:04:25.339
Count your blessings.

00:04:25.339 --> 00:04:27.519
The songwriter said, name them one by one

00:04:27.519 --> 00:04:30.799
and it will surprise you what the Lord hath done.

00:04:30.799 --> 00:04:32.980
And so often we think about the blessings,

00:04:32.980 --> 00:04:35.079
even as we talked about, I mentioned it already

00:04:35.079 --> 00:04:38.959
this morning, the Lord, he daily loadeth us with benefits

00:04:38.959 --> 00:04:40.359
and he's been so good to us.

00:04:40.359 --> 00:04:42.880
If we're not careful, we can focus on some challenges

00:04:42.880 --> 00:04:45.359
and some difficulties and the obstacles.

00:04:45.359 --> 00:04:47.279
But God says that we're to fix our attention

00:04:47.279 --> 00:04:49.760
on the blessings and thank God for what he's done.

00:04:49.760 --> 00:04:52.600
In 2019, we turn to the book of Ephesians,

00:04:52.600 --> 00:04:56.040
be strong in the Lord and the power of his might.

00:04:56.040 --> 00:04:58.880
Listen, we're engaged in spiritual warfare

00:04:58.880 --> 00:05:01.320
and we need to understand that the battles

00:05:01.320 --> 00:05:04.600
in which we're facing, the battles in which we're engaged in

00:05:04.600 --> 00:05:07.559
as Tozer said, the Christian life can best be described

00:05:07.559 --> 00:05:10.480
not as a playground, but as a battleground.

00:05:11.200 --> 00:05:14.239
We are engaged in spiritual warfare

00:05:14.239 --> 00:05:19.239
and the truth is that we must be strong in the Lord.

00:05:19.239 --> 00:05:21.559
2020, looking unto Jesus.

00:05:21.559 --> 00:05:23.959
Oh, 2020 was what a year that was.

00:05:23.959 --> 00:05:28.959
And God gave me that theme about October 5th or so of 2019.

00:05:29.200 --> 00:05:32.480
I had no idea of all that we would deal with in 2020,

00:05:32.480 --> 00:05:35.760
but how encouraged I was personally

00:05:35.760 --> 00:05:37.640
that as we develop that theme,

00:05:37.640 --> 00:05:39.619
that we're to keep our eyes on Jesus.

00:05:39.619 --> 00:05:42.820
He knows all things, he do with all things well,

00:05:42.820 --> 00:05:44.140
and we're to keep our eyes on him.

00:05:44.140 --> 00:05:48.019
2021, complete in Christ from the book of Colossians.

00:05:48.019 --> 00:05:51.540
And I'm thankful that my identity first and foremost

00:05:51.540 --> 00:05:55.059
is in Christ and I am complete in him.

00:05:55.059 --> 00:05:57.500
And what a blessing to know the Lord Jesus Christ

00:05:57.500 --> 00:05:59.019
