00:06:11.179 --> 00:06:13.100
He came in here not knowing the Lord,

00:06:13.100 --> 00:06:14.779
but left here knowing the Lord

00:06:14.779 --> 00:06:17.980
and being confident that heaven was his home

00:06:17.980 --> 00:06:19.779
and his identity is in Christ.

00:06:19.779 --> 00:06:23.260
And I'm so thankful to be complete in Christ.

00:06:23.260 --> 00:06:28.119
2022, we went to the book of 1 John, walking in the light.

00:06:28.119 --> 00:06:30.859
Aren't you thankful that we can have fellowship with God?

00:06:30.859 --> 00:06:32.380
We can have fellowship with God.

00:06:32.380 --> 00:06:35.100
And we walk in the light as he is in the light.

00:06:35.100 --> 00:06:37.739
And what a blessing to know the Lord

00:06:37.739 --> 00:06:39.339
and to walk with him daily,

00:06:39.339 --> 00:06:44.339
to develop our personal relationship with him

00:06:44.339 --> 00:06:46.179
and certainly a blessing.

00:06:46.179 --> 00:06:49.500
Last year or this year, still 2023, great is the Lord.

00:06:49.500 --> 00:06:51.779
And throughout the calendar year of 2023,

00:06:51.779 --> 00:06:55.779
we dealt with examining, discovering, if you will,

00:06:55.779 --> 00:06:57.059
why God is great.

00:06:57.059 --> 00:06:59.820
Why do we say, why does the scripture declare

00:06:59.820 --> 00:07:00.779
that God is great?

00:07:00.779 --> 00:07:02.459
Why would the psalmist stand up and say,

00:07:02.459 --> 00:07:05.019
great is the Lord and greatly to be praised?

00:07:05.019 --> 00:07:07.660
Well, God has revealed, he's declared to us in his word,

00:07:08.459 --> 00:07:11.179
his greatness and we study for a large portion

00:07:11.179 --> 00:07:15.540
of this calendar year, reasons that God is great.

00:07:15.540 --> 00:07:19.339
And then we said this, as we continue to look at the idea

00:07:19.339 --> 00:07:20.739
of discovering his greatness,

00:07:20.739 --> 00:07:23.140
then we're to declare his greatness

00:07:23.140 --> 00:07:26.579
because not everyone knows how great our God is.

00:07:26.579 --> 00:07:28.459
A lot of people in our world that have no idea

00:07:28.459 --> 00:07:30.260
how great our savior is.

00:07:30.260 --> 00:07:32.619
And what a blessing that God has given us

00:07:32.619 --> 00:07:36.140
the opportunity to know him and then to declare

00:07:36.140 --> 00:07:39.899
his greatness and then we finished up the calendar year

00:07:39.899 --> 00:07:43.339
by dealing with the impact that his greatness will have

00:07:43.339 --> 00:07:45.540
in our lives daily.

00:07:45.540 --> 00:07:48.619
When I truly understand how great God is,

00:07:48.619 --> 00:07:53.619
my belief, God is great, will impact my behavior.

00:07:53.779 --> 00:07:57.179
How I behave reveals what I believe.

00:07:57.179 --> 00:07:59.980
The way that we pray is going to be impacted

00:07:59.980 --> 00:08:02.500
by how great we believe God is.

00:08:02.500 --> 00:08:04.059
And we dealt with a number of things.

00:08:04.059 --> 00:08:06.940
And so this year in 2024,

00:08:06.940 --> 00:08:08.700
as we flip the calendar tomorrow,

00:08:08.700 --> 00:08:10.940
as we have our vision Sunday today

00:08:10.940 --> 00:08:14.380
and introduce the theme, the idea of continue.

00:08:14.380 --> 00:08:16.859
And again, I mentioned 2 Timothy 3, 14,

00:08:16.859 --> 00:08:18.779
you probably, some of you can read it from where you are.

00:08:18.779 --> 00:08:21.019
Some of you say it's just blurry to me

00:08:21.019 --> 00:08:23.540
because of the size of the font there.

00:08:23.540 --> 00:08:25.299
But 2 Timothy 3 and verse number 14,

00:08:25.299 --> 00:08:27.859
Paul gives this charge to Timothy and he says this,

00:08:27.859 --> 00:08:31.940
but continue thou in the things which now has learned

00:08:31.980 --> 00:08:33.619
and has been assured of,

00:08:33.619 --> 00:08:37.260
knowing of whom thou has learned them.

00:08:37.260 --> 00:08:39.659
The word continue means to persevere.

00:08:39.659 --> 00:08:43.059
It means to be steadfast or constant in any course.

00:08:43.059 --> 00:08:46.419
It carries this idea not to depart.

00:08:46.419 --> 00:08:49.140
The idea of continue in Acts chapter 14 and verse 22,

00:08:49.140 --> 00:08:50.419
you don't need to turn there.

00:08:50.419 --> 00:08:51.739
But in that portion of scripture,

00:08:51.739 --> 00:08:54.820
Paul has the opportunity to follow up

00:08:54.820 --> 00:08:56.340
with those that had been saved

00:08:56.340 --> 00:08:57.859
during the first missionary journey,

00:08:57.859 --> 00:08:59.340
those that were reached with the gospel

00:08:59.340 --> 00:09:00.859
of the Lord Jesus Christ.

00:09:00.859 --> 00:09:03.099
And the Bible tells us in Acts 14 and verse 22

00:09:03.099 --> 00:09:06.059
that when Paul followed up with those believers,

00:09:06.059 --> 00:09:08.500
that he gave them this exhortation

00:09:08.500 --> 00:09:11.500
that they would continue in the faith.

00:09:11.500 --> 00:09:14.580
We find that each letter of this first and second Timothy,

00:09:14.580 --> 00:09:18.260
these letters that we'll be studying this year in 2024,

00:09:18.260 --> 00:09:21.299
we find that God would use the apostle Paul

00:09:21.299 --> 00:09:22.900
to write to Timothy.

00:09:22.900 --> 00:09:25.140
And we find that in each of these books,

00:09:25.140 --> 00:09:28.020
there's a charge to continue.

00:09:28.020 --> 00:09:31.500
We find that there are some that are in the scriptures.

00:09:31.500 --> 00:09:33.619
In fact, some that are mentioned by name

00:09:33.619 --> 00:09:35.219
throughout the scriptures,

00:09:35.219 --> 00:09:38.140
who unfortunately they failed to continue.

00:09:38.140 --> 00:09:42.099
They gave up, they went back and they did not continue.

00:09:42.099 --> 00:09:44.859
And we find that as believers,

00:09:44.859 --> 00:09:47.140
we understand this morning that we have an enemy.

00:09:47.140 --> 00:09:50.940
I mentioned from a previous year in 2019,

00:09:50.940 --> 00:09:52.780
when we spoke about be strong in the Lord,

00:09:52.780 --> 00:09:55.219
that we are engaged in spiritual warfare

00:09:55.219 --> 00:09:56.299
and spiritual battle.

00:09:56.380 --> 00:09:58.099
And we have an enemy.

00:09:58.099 --> 00:10:00.059
The ultimate goal of Satan.

00:10:00.059 --> 00:10:03.099
is to devour you, to devour us.

00:10:03.099 --> 00:10:05.859
The Bible says that he's walking about seeking

00:10:05.859 --> 00:10:09.139
whom he may devour.

00:10:09.139 --> 00:10:11.179
We understand that's in 1 Peter 5,

00:10:11.179 --> 00:10:13.099
a book that's written to believers.

00:10:13.099 --> 00:10:15.439
We understand that his work amongst lost people,

00:10:15.439 --> 00:10:18.379
those that have not yet trusted Christ as their savior,

00:10:18.379 --> 00:10:21.759
is to keep them blinded to the truth of the gospel.

00:10:21.759 --> 00:10:24.699
The Bible tells us in 2 Corinthians 4,

00:10:24.699 --> 00:10:25.979
in whom the God of this world

00:10:25.979 --> 00:10:28.579
hath blinded the minds of them which believe not,

00:10:28.579 --> 00:10:30.259
lest the light of the glorious gospel

00:10:30.259 --> 00:10:31.859
should shine in unto them.

00:10:31.859 --> 00:10:36.019
And we find that Satan is actively working along the way

00:10:36.019 --> 00:10:39.419
with his ultimate goal of devouring you and devouring me.

00:10:39.419 --> 00:10:43.699
He seeks to discourage and derail God's people.

00:10:43.699 --> 00:10:45.219
He seeks to discourage you.

00:10:45.219 --> 00:10:47.019
He'll use a variety of means.

00:10:47.019 --> 00:10:49.099
In fact, as you study throughout the scriptures,

00:10:49.099 --> 00:10:52.619
as you begin to look at life and even your own experiences,

00:10:52.619 --> 00:10:55.019
the means that he uses are varied.

00:10:55.019 --> 00:11:00.019
And unfortunately, he's been successful.

00:11:01.219 --> 00:11:03.059
He's been successful far more often

00:11:03.059 --> 00:11:06.180
than any of us would really like to acknowledge.

00:11:06.180 --> 00:11:08.459
There are people that we can read of in the scriptures

00:11:08.459 --> 00:11:09.779
that did not continue.

00:11:09.779 --> 00:11:11.500
They gave up, they went back.

00:11:12.860 --> 00:11:15.540
There are people that you know, that I know,

00:11:15.540 --> 00:11:17.199
that did not continue.

00:11:17.199 --> 00:11:19.579
They've given up, they've turned back.

00:11:19.579 --> 00:11:21.000
And that's unfortunate.

00:11:21.000 --> 00:11:24.139
But we understand this morning that we have an enemy.

00:11:24.139 --> 00:11:26.019
And he uses a variety of means

00:11:26.019 --> 00:11:28.739
in order to try to discourage the people of God

00:11:28.739 --> 00:11:30.500
and to derail the people of God.

00:11:30.500 --> 00:11:32.339
But I'm thankful that the Bible tells us

00:11:32.339 --> 00:11:33.860
that greater is he that is in you

00:11:33.860 --> 00:11:35.379
than he that is in the world.

00:11:35.379 --> 00:11:38.619
I'm thankful this morning that God has given us a Bible

00:11:38.619 --> 00:11:41.540
and he loves us as his people, as his children.

